column3: Half Time / Full Time - Liverpool / Liverpool
column13: Liverpool is coming off a run of excellent results and an ongoing unbeaten run of 17 games.They lead the Premier League and are perfect in the Champions League, with 12 goals and only one conceded.The team is unbeaten in their last ten away games, winning eight times and scoring at least three goals in seven of them.Despite some defensive problems in their last away games, the English grand is the favourite against the unconvincing Girona, who have defensive problems and a poor Champions League record.

We expect Atalanta to have an advantage against Real Madrid due to their strong performance in Europe, being one of the three teams without defeat in the Champions League.Their aggressive style of play and excellent press positioning will create problems for Real, who have some key players questionable, such as Bellingham, Vinicius and Rodrigo.Furthermore, Real Madrid's problems in the Champions League and their difficulty in controlling the game will make it difficult for them to counter Atalanta's strong pressing, which plays with confidence and high intensity.

Celtic are in excellent form, having not lost in their last 14 games and have 14 wins in 15 games in the Scottish Premiership.They are favourites to win against Dinamo Zagreb, who are in poor form and have not won in their last 5 games.Dynamo have problems with scoring as they have scored only 3 goals in their last 5 games.In addition, Celtic are coming off a convincing 3-0 win against Hibernian and will travel to Zagreb with high confidence and a strong performance in their last games.

Brest have failed to keep a dry net in their last 10 games, scoring more than 3 goals in 6 of them.Furthermore, they have conceded an average of more than two goals per game in the last five matches.On the other hand, PSV have shown excellent form in attack, scoring at least 3 goals in 6 of their last 8 games and their last two Champions League games have also ended with more than 3 goals.The game is expected to be a high scoring one, with plenty of goals from both sides.

Inter are in great form, unbeaten in their last 13 games and are the only team in the Champions League who have yet to concede a goal.They are second in the group with 13 points, just two behind Liverpool, and are on a run of 5 consecutive Serie A wins.Simone Inzaghi's side feature an excellent defence, while the attack is also effective as they beat Parma 3-1.However, Bayer Leverkusen have injury problems in attack as both their main strikers, Boniface and Schick, are out of action, giving Inter the advantage.

Shakhtar Donetsk is on a run of high scoring games, with 4 of their last 5 games ending with 4 or more goals.They have scored at least one goal in 9 of their last 10 games and will look to score against Bayern as well.Bayern Munich is one of the best attacking teams in the Bundesliga and Champions League, having scored 3 or more goals in 11 of their last 22 games.Furthermore, Bayern have failed to keep a dry net in their last three games, suggesting that Shakhtar will score as well.The probability of more than 3.5 goals is high.

Club Brugge are in great form, having scored 9 goals in their last 3 games and will look to keep scoring against Sporting.On the other hand, Sporting have been struggling, but despite that, there have been at least 3 goals in 8 of their last 9 Champions League games.Sporting's defensive problems, combined with Brugge's attacking capabilities, suggest that both teams will be able to get off the mark.
